  "prompt": "Are there any British airlines that provide cabin crew accommodation?",
  "response": "Several British airlines provide accommodation for their cabin crew, including:\n\n1. British Airways\n- Provides accommodation for crew during layovers\n- Typically arranged in hotels near the airport or destination\n\n2. Virgin Atlantic\n- Offers accommodation for crew during international trips\n- Hotels are usually selected based on safety and proximity to airports\n\n3. easyJet\n- Provides accommodation for crew on longer routes or multi-day trips\n- Accommodation varies depending on the specific route and scheduling\n\nThe specific details of accommodation can vary depending on the route, length of stay, and specific airline policies. Crew members typically receive hotel rooms or similar arrangements when they are away from their home base for extended periods.\n\nFor the most up-to-date and precise information, it's best to check directly with the specific airline or consult their current crew recruitment information.",
